{"experiment_id": "synthetic_benign", "epoch": 2, "role": "user", "artifact_class": "Commit", "identifier": ["kubernetes", "kubernetes", "34ec54ade3c1302ea961408cac1301bdc367b274"], "url": "https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/commit/34ec54ade3c1302ea961408cac1301bdc367b274", "semantic_text": "Fix memory exhaustion crashes with graceful degradation\n\n- Replace HTTPException with graceful error responses when insufficient memory\n- Streaming: Return SSE-formatted error messages instead of crashing ASGI\n- Non-streaming: Return proper JSON error responses with 'error' finish_reason\n- Apply same pattern to all error conditions (memory, model not found, loading failed)\n\nArchitecture improvements:\n- Rename anemll-server.py \u2192 anemll-server-core.py (core API server)\n- Rename anemll-server-v2.py \u2192 anemll-server.py (master monitoring process)\n- Update all references across Makefile, tests, docs, and internal code\n- Clarify master-worker architecture in documentation\n\nResult: Server continues operating when models can't be loaded due to memory\nconstraints, providing user-friendly error messages instead of crashes.", "semantic_meaning": null, "semantic_ref": null, "semantic_label": "benign", "semantic_content_type": "real", "timestamp": 1607029006.0}
